  "text": "The error estimates are derived in the weighted Sobolev spaces L 2 (C Y , y α ) and H 1 (C Y , y α ), and they are valid under the condition that neighboring elements have comparable size in the extended n + 1-dimension (see [CITATION_1] ). This is a mild assumption that includes general meshes which do not satisfy the so-called shape-regularity assumption, i.e., mesh refinements for which the quotient between outer and inner diameter of the elements does not remain bounded (see [CITATION_2] Chapter 4] ).",
